          <h4>Size-level stock availability</h4>
          <p>AboutYou displays per-size stock counts on PDP — could be captured as an additional field per variant row.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="impr-tag easy">Easy</span>
      </div>
      <div class="impr-card">
        <div class="impr-info">
          <h4>Product description (long-form)</h4>
          <p>Full marketing descriptions exist on PDP but aren't currently in the schema; fill rate for description field is currently 0%.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="impr-tag easy">Easy</span>
      </div>
      <div class="impr-card">
        <div class="impr-info">
          <h4>Promotion end date</h4>
          <p>Countdown timers shown on sale items indicate a promotion end date — field exists in schema but is not yet populated.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="impr-tag medium">Medium</span>
      </div>
      <div class="impr-card">
        <div class="impr-info">
          <h4>Merchant / seller attribution</h4>
          <p>AboutYou operates as a multi-vendor marketplace — merchant_name and merchant_url fields could be populated for third-party sellers.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="impr-tag medium">Medium</span>
      </div>
      <div class="impr-card">
        <div class="impr-info">
          <h4>Price-per-unit (ppu) and unit_type</h4>
          <p>For applicable categories (fragrances, cosmetics), PPU is shown on site and can be extracted as a separate data point.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="impr-tag medium">Medium</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="note-box">
      <strong>Note on pricing:</strong> AboutYou displays both a full price and a promotional price where sales apply. The dataset captures both <code>full_price</code> and <code>price</code> — when no promotion is active they are identical; during sales, <code>price</code> reflects the discounted value and <code>promotion_type</code> is set to "SALE".
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- DELIVERY -->
<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label">08 — File delivery</div>
    <h2>S3 delivery path</h2>
    <div class="code-block">
      <span class="key">s3://</span><span class="accent">reinox-datasets</span>/<span class="key">sellers</span>/YOUR_SELLER_ID/<span class="key">contracts</span>/YOUR_CONTRACT_ID/<span class="accent">aboutyou</span>/<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="accent">data_file.txt</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:var(--muted)">← pipe-delimited, UTF-8, 545,866 rows</span><br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="accent">brand_counts.csv</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:var(--muted)">← 2,522 brands with row counts</span><br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="accent">fill_rate_report.csv</span>&nbsp;<span style="color:var(--muted)">← per-field fill rates</span>
    </div>
